other_tests.findings: Dilated fluid-filled appendix measuring up to 10 mm with hyperemic wall and extensive periappendiceal fat stranding. Associated wall thickening of the base of the cecum likely reactive. No evidence of abscess formation or perforation. Bibasilar dependent atelectasis in lung bases. Multiple focal hepatic hypodensities likely representing cysts or hamartomas. Imaged bowel loops normal in caliber. Mild ectasia of the infrarenal aorta.
